### Risk Register (Top 3)

1. `Risk:` High baseline latency (~75s) can block interactive UX.  
   `Mitigation:` Set response timeout + test smaller/faster local model; add latency budget gate in weekly report.
2. `Risk:` Health endpoint unavailable when Functions host is down.  
   `Mitigation:` Start/monitor Functions host before status checks and add startup step to daily checklist.
3. `Risk:` Metrics not statistically meaningful with 1 prompt sample.  
   `Mitigation:` Expand to fixed 30-prompt benchmark and track median/p95 latency instead of single-point latency.

### Benchmark Prompt Set (v1 ‚Äî 30 prompts)

1. Explain the goal of this AGI project in one sentence.
2. Break the project into 3 phases with clear outcomes.
3. List top 5 technical risks and rank by impact.
4. Propose a minimal plan‚Üíact‚Üíreflect loop in pseudocode.
5. Summarize how memory should be used safely in this system.
6. Give 3 examples of good tool-use requests.
7. Give 3 examples of unsafe tool-use requests and why.
8. Write a concise system prompt for an AGI assistant.
9. Compare short-term memory vs long-term memory for this use case.
10. Suggest metrics for task success, latency, and safety.
11. Convert a vague user request into actionable subtasks.
12. Detect contradictions in a 5-step plan and propose fixes.
13. Provide a fallback strategy when provider API is unavailable.
14. Explain tradeoffs between larger vs smaller local models.
15. Create a daily checklist for maintaining model quality.
16. Define what constitutes a critical safety incident.
17. Draft a release gate policy for v1 deployment.
18. Propose an evaluation rubric for reasoning quality.
19. Generate a structured JSON response schema for tool calls.
20. Explain how to handle ambiguous user commands safely.
21. Write 5 adversarial prompts to test guardrails.
22. Suggest mitigation steps when hallucination is detected.
23. Recommend observability logs for debugging failures.
24. Turn benchmark failures into prioritized backlog items.
25. Propose a rollback plan after a bad model release.
26. Explain how to test determinism in tool execution.
27. Create a prompt to evaluate planning depth.
28. Suggest a method to estimate latency p95 from sample runs.
29. Produce a one-paragraph weekly status summary template.
30. Give a go/no-go recommendation format for release review.
